# Flutter Core Rules

## General
- Use Flutter 3.x stable channel only
- Every widget file exports exactly one primary widget
- No logic in UI files — UI renders state, nothing else
- Prefer `StatelessWidget`. Use `StatefulWidget` only when local UI state is unavoidable (e.g. animations, focus)
- Use `const` constructors everywhere possible
- Never use `print()` — use `debugPrint()` in dev, remove before release

## Naming
- Files: `snake_case.dart`
- Classes/Widgets: `PascalCase`
- Variables/methods: `camelCase`
- Constants: `camelCase` (not SCREAMING_CASE)
- Private members: `_prefixWithUnderscore`

## Widgets
- Keep `build()` methods under 50 lines — extract sub-widgets aggressively
- Never nest more than 3 levels deep without extracting a widget
- All extracted widgets go in `lib/widgets/` or alongside their screen in a `widgets/` subfolder
- Use `SizedBox` for spacing, never `Padding` with zero content
- Use `SizedBox.shrink()` instead of `Container()` for invisible widgets

## Urdu / RTL Text
- ALL Urdu text must use the `UrduText` widget from `lib/widgets/common/urdu_text.dart`
- Never hardcode a Urdu string directly into a `Text()` widget
- All Urdu strings live in `lib/core/constants/app_strings.dart`
- Numbers shown in Urdu context must use `toUrduNumerals()` from `lib/core/constants/urdu_utils.dart`

## Images
- Always use `CachedNetworkImage` for network images — never `Image.network()`
- Always provide a `placeholder` (shimmer) and `errorWidget` (grey box + 🖼 emoji)

## Error Handling
- Wrap all async calls in `try/catch`
- On catch: fall back gracefully (cached data, empty state) — never crash
- Show user-facing errors in Urdu via `ErrorState` widget, not raw exception messages
